quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,154,"What is [wrong] with you? How do you make judgement?"
  37,155,"Then will you not be reminded?"
  37,156,"Or do you have a clear authority?{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., evidence.]
  43,43,"So adhere to that which is revealed to you. Indeed, you are on a straight path."
  43,44,"And indeed, it is a remembrance{1} for you and your people, and you [all] are going to be questioned.",footnotes:1:[i.e., an honor.  Or "a reminder."]
  43,45,"And ask those We sent before you of Our messengers; have We made besides the Most Merciful deities to be worshipped?"
  44,28,"Thus. And We caused to inherit it another people."
  44,29,"And the heaven and earth wept not for them, nor were they reprieved."
  44,30,"And We certainly saved the Children of Israel from the humiliating torment -"
  45,19,"Indeed, they will never avail you against Allāh at all. And indeed, the wrongdoers are allies of one another; but Allāh is the protector of the righteous."
  45,20,"This [Qur’ān] is enlightenment for mankind and guidance and mercy for a people who are certain [in faith]."
  45,21,"Or do those who commit evils think We will make them like those who have believed and done righteous deeds - [make them] equal in their life and their death?{1} Evil is that which they judge [i.e., assume].",footnotes:1:[Another meaning is "...[the evildoers being] equal in their life and their death," i.e., unresponsive to guidance.]
  46,7,"And when Our verses are recited to them as clear evidences, those who disbelieve say of the truth when it has come to them, "
  46,8,"Or do they say, ",footnotes:1:[Of false implications and suggestions.]
  46,9,"Say, ",footnotes:1:[i.e., I am neither the first messenger to be sent, nor do I bring something different from the other messengers.]
